Interests and hobbies were never thought to be more than just that. I was so worried about not having to be on food pantry lines again but as an adult that I never put any thought into it  Then after realizing I had no direction, just feeling fear. Now I feel like I'm nowhere.

As I got older I realized these things I thought I wanted to be or do weren't true. But now I am left feeling aimless. With thoughts of "the chance of being a successful enough artist that can afford to live is slim, better to choose something practical"

Poverty is very traumatic for many reasons but growing up I wasn't encouraged to find a passion, I was encouraged to get good grades so I could get a decent paying job so I wouldn't be poor. It was never a question of what I wanted to do it was question of what paid the most.

It amazes me that some people knew what their passion was as a kid and I feel like most people know what their passion is by young adulthood. But I have no fucking idea and have not the slightest inkling.
